                    },
                    "body": "ZF-7288 would fix ZF-7217, too",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mabe",
                        "name": "mabe",
                        "displayName": "Marc Bennewitz (private)",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-07-15T12:58:44.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-07-15T12:58:44.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/35977",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=gog",
                        "name": "gog",
                        "displayName": "Goran Juric",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "As much as I can see from the PHP docs, there is no need for error suppression in the else block.\r\n\r\nsession_start() returns either true or false in PHP 5.3\r\n\r\nI guess this is not the only thing that should change with 5.3 becoming more and more popular. I think there should be a single place where we could document issues like this one, so once the 5.3 becomes a requirement for running ZF we can get rid of the BC code.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=gog",
                        "name": "gog",
                        "displayName": "Goran Juric",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-11-12T14:54:48.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-11-12T14:54:48.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/50898",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=adamlundrigan",
                        "name": "adamlundrigan",
                        "displayName": "Adam Lundrigan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "But it restores the error handler right after:\r\n{code}\r\nif (self::$_throwStartupExceptions) {\r\n    require_once 'Zend\/Session\/Exception.php';\r\n    set_error_handler(array('Zend_Session_Exception', 'handleSessionStartError'), $errorLevel);\r\n}\r\n\r\n$startedCleanly = session_start();\r\n\r\nif (self::$_throwStartupExceptions) {\r\n    restore_error_handler();\r\n}\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nSo I don't see what the issue is.  Could someone provide an example of why this behavior is bad\/wrong?\r\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=adamlundrigan",
                        "name": "adamlundrigan",
                        "displayName": "Adam Lundrigan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2012-05-31T14:25:46.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2012-05-31T14:25:46.000+0000"
                }
            ]
        }
    },
